  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (configuration gap probe)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CFD solver exposes three tunable configuration parameters—base mesh element size (h_base), turbulence model closure coefficient C_mu, and hemolysis power-law threshold strain-rate gamma_th—that govern prediction fidelity. Validation runs were executed at analyst-chosen settings (h_base = 0.35 mm, C_mu = 0.09, gamma_th = 500 s⁻¹); results are reported 'at the chosen settings'. No configuration-binding node links these values to the deployment specification, and the Context of Use places no constraint on which parameter values must be used during regulatory submission runs.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-worst-case-hemolysis-identification",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-fda-pump-geometry-v2",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-experimental-hemolysis-nib-2013",
