      "name": "Hemolysis power-law threshold validation at gamma_th = 500 s⁻¹",
      "description": "The hemolysis scalar transport model applies a strain-rate threshold gamma_th below which erythrocyte damage accumulation is suppressed. Validation against five operating-point measurements from the FDA benchmark dataset was performed at gamma_th = 500 s⁻¹, yielding RH < 1 at all conditions. The threshold value is documented in the validation report narrative but is not pinned in any machine-readable configuration record linked to this package, leaving deployment-time selection to analyst discretion.",
